== Prepare Veggies ==

If you don't have a #microwave oven{}, heat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas 
mark 7 for the tortillas.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin 
strips, then cut the strips in half.

Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Make Dressing ==

In a #small bowl{}, mix together the @rice vinegar{15%ml}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and 
@olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} - this is your dressing.

== Cook Beef ==

Heat a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and pepper. Fry until browned, 
about ~{5-6%minutes}.

Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Once browned, drain and discard any excess fat from the beef.

Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in the @hoisin sauce{64%g} and cook until sticky, ~{30%seconds}, then 
remove from the heat.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Warm Tortillas and Toss ==

Pile the @plain taco tortillas{6} onto a #plate{}. Heat them through in the 
microwave, 850W: ~{50%seconds} / 750W: ~{1%minute}, until warm and soft.

If you're using the oven, lay the tortillas onto a #baking tray{} and place on 
the middle shelf to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the baby gem lettuce to the dressing and toss together.

== Assemble Tacos ==

Lay the tortillas on your #plates{} and spread each with some @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}.

Top with the hoisin beef and baby gem - as much as you'd like.

> TIP: Tacos are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in!